Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: ModuleNotFoundError for matplotlib or pandas

Solution: Install required packages: pip3 install matplotlib pandas seaborn numpy
Issue: JSON decode errors when loading data

Solution: Verify JSON files are properly formatted. Use python3 -m json.tool filename.json to validate
Issue: Charts not displaying or saving

Solution: Ensure reports directory exists and has write permissions. Check matplotlib backend with plt.get_backend()
Issue: Division by zero in score calculations

Solution: Add validation checks for zero values before division operations. Use default values for missing data
Issue: Assessment results showing unrealistic scores

Solution: Review data generation logic and ensure metrics are within valid ranges (0-100). Check weight calculations sum to 1.0
